\c 2
\s1 Judgement even for those without the written law
\rem /s1 The Righteous Judgment of God; God's Righteous Judgment; God's Judgment of Sin
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 2:1: \xt Mat 7:1; Luk 6:37.\x*SoВҰ105690 there's no excuse for anyone who judges others becauseВҰ105709 you're condemningВҰ105707 yourselvesВҰ105706 if you're doingВҰ105711 those same things that you're judging other for
\v 2 because weВҰ105714 know that God's judgementВҰ105719 is based on the factual accounts of what \add each person\add* is doing.
\v 3 ButВҰ105742 maybe you'reВҰ105731 thinking that you can judge others doingВҰ105743 these things and yet \add somehow\add* escapeВҰ105747 God's judgementВҰ105749 when you do them yourselfВҰ105744?
\v 4 Or maybe you'reВҰ105764 \add taking advantage\add* of God's kindness and patienceВҰ105763 without realising that hisВҰ105757 kindness was \add meant\add* to lead you towards repentanceВҰ105772?
\v 5 ButВҰ105780 it's yourВҰ105779 hardnessВҰ105778 and failure to repent that \add causing\add* severe anger to be stored up for the day of God's judgementВҰ105794 when \add all\add* will be revealed \add including\add* his severe anger
\v 6 \x + \xo 2:6: \xt Psa 62:12; Prv 24:12.\x*as each person will be \add judged\add* by their actions.
