\v 8 but those who've \add lived out\add* their selfishВҰ105821 ambitionВҰ105821 and refused to believe the truthВҰ105826 but \add let themselves get\add* persuadedВҰ105827 by disobedience, \add will meet with\add* severeВҰ105832 angerВҰ105832 and rageВҰ105834.
\v 9 For everyВҰ105840 person doing evilВҰ105846, there will be tribulation and distressВҰ105838вҖ”to Jews firstВҰ105849 and then to non-Jews,
\v 10 butВҰ105854 to those who do goodВҰ105862, there'll be praise and honourВҰ105855 and peaceВҰ105857вҖ”to Jews firstВҰ105865 and then to non-Jews
\v 11 \x + \xo 2:11: \xt Deu 10:17.\x*becauseВҰ105869 \nd GodВҰ105874\nd* doesn't \add indulge in\add* favouritismВҰ105871.
\p
\v 12 Those not under the \add Jewish\add* laws and yet sinned, they'll be judged without the law, and those who knew the laws and sinned, will be judged by the law,
\v 13 becauseВҰ105891 listeningВҰ105893 to the law doesn't make \add people\add* rightВҰ105896 with \nd GodВҰ105899\nd*, butВҰ105900 rather it's those who obey the law who will be declared guiltless.
\v 14 Whenever other nations don't have \add Jewish\add* law but naturallyВҰ105913 obey what's in the laws, then even those thatВҰ105909 don't have \add our\add* laws have their own law.
\v 15 They demonstrate that they effectively have \add God's\add* law writtenВҰ105932 in their minds and which matches their consciencesВҰ105940, and betweenВҰ105942 the two they'll be either accusedВҰ105946 or defendedВҰ105949
\v 16 on the dayВҰ105952 when \nd GodВҰ105958\nd* through \nd MessiahВҰ105968 Yeshua\nd*, judges people'sВҰ105962 private \add lives\add* as I've shared \add as part of\add* the goodВҰ105965 messageВҰ105965.
\s1 Jews who disobey their laws
\rem /s1 The Jews and their law
\p
\v 17 ButВҰ105977 if you're a Jew and trusting in the law and boastingВҰ105982 about \add beingВҰ105976 chosen by\add* \nd GodВҰ105984\nd*
\v 18 and knowing his will and knowing what's important because of familiarity with the law,
\v 19 and if you've persuadedВҰ105997 yourselfВҰ105999 that you're a guideВҰ106000 for the blindВҰ106002 and a lightВҰ106003 to those who are in darknessВҰ106006,
\v 20 and that you're an instructorВҰ106007 to foolishВҰ106008 people and a teacherВҰ106009 of children, and that you appearВҰ106013 to be knowledgeableВҰ106015 about the truthВҰ106018 of the law,
\v 21 then why do you teach others when you haven't \add even\add* taughtВҰ106024 yourselfВҰ106026? You announce that stealing is wrong, but you'reВҰ106033 a thief.
\v 22 You teach about not messing with other people's spouses, yet you do it yourself. You detestВҰ106040 idolsВҰ106042, but you sneak money out of the templeВҰ106043.
