\q2
\v 17 theyВҰ106396 don'tВҰ106395 know the pathВҰ106393 \add that leads to\add* peaceВҰ106394.вҖҷ
\q2
\v 18 \x + \xo 3:18: \xt Psa 36:1.\x*Revering \nd GodВҰ106400\nd* isn't at the frontВҰ106401 of theirВҰ106404 \add minds\add*.
\p
\v 19 We know that whatever the law says, it's for \add everyoneВҰ106419\add* that the law applies to, so that no one can speakВҰ106417 against it, andВҰ106422 the whole worldВҰ106427 will be bound by God's judgementВҰ106423.
\v 20 \x + \xo 3:20: \xt Psa 143:2; Gal 2:16.\x*No human will be declared guiltless in front of God by their keeping the law, becauseВҰ106441 it's the law that teaches what sinВҰ106444 is.
\s1 Removing the guilt from sin
\rem /s1 Righteousness through Faith; How We Are Put Right with God; Christ Took Our Punishment
\p
\v 21 ButВҰ106456 now \nd GodВҰ106450\nd* has revealedВҰ106451 a way to remove guilt that's not by rulesвҖ”a way that Mosheh andВҰ106456 the prophetsВҰ106458 wrote about.
\v 22 \x + \xo 3:22: \xt Gal 2:16.\x*We can be made rightВҰ106459 with \nd GodВҰ106461\nd* throughВҰ106462 faithВҰ106463 in \nd Yeshua MessiahВҰ106466\nd*. This is for \em \+nd everyoneВҰ106466\+nd*\em* who believesВҰ106475 becauseВҰ106477 there'sВҰ106478 no distinctionВҰ106479 \add between Jews andВҰ106460 others\add*
\v 23 becauseВҰ106481 everyone has sinnedВҰ106482 andВҰ106483 is unable to be honoured by \nd GodВҰ106489\nd*.
\v 24 \add But\add* even without deserving it, we can be declared guiltless by God's graceВҰ106494 by beingВҰ106490 bought out of slavery \add to sin\add* by \nd MessiahВҰ106500 Yeshua\nd*
\v 25 who God placed \add on the altar\add* as a sacrifice for sin. \add This happensВҰ106524\add* throughВҰ106507 faithВҰ106509 in his bloodВҰ106514 which was a signВҰ106516 of his sinlessness.
\p (God hasn't yet judged those who sinned in the past
\v 26 because of his patience, waiting for the presentВҰ106539 timeВҰ106540 to show his righteousnessВҰ106535 and to be fair, and to remove the guilt of those with faithВҰ106550 in \nd YeshuaВҰ106551\nd*.)
\p
\v 27 SoВҰ106553 whereВҰ106552 does that leave boastingВҰ106555? It's not in the picture. How come? ThroughВҰ106557 obeying the \add Mosheh's\add* laws? No, throughВҰ106564 a law about faithВҰ106566.
\v 28 SoВҰ106569 now weВҰ106567 should expect that a personВҰ106573 will be made guiltless by faithВҰ106572вҖ”not by obeying \add Mosheh's\add* laws.
\v 29 Or is \nd GodВҰ106581\nd* only god of the Jews? Isn't he also the god of others? Yes, he is the god of others.
\v 30 \x + \xo 3:30: \xt Deu 6:4; Gal 3:20.\x*Indeed, there's only one \nd GodВҰ106595\nd* and he declares people guiltless by faith whether they're circumcisedВҰ106598 Jews, or non-Jews.
\v 31 SoВҰ106607 does this вҖҳfaithВҰ106611вҖҷ cancel the law? Not on your life. In fact, itВҰ106614 upholds the law.
\c 4
\s1 Abraham's faith
