\p
\v 1 SoВҰ106619 what did ourВҰ106626 physical ancestor, AbrahamВҰ106622 discover about all this?
\v 2 BecauseВҰ106631 if AbrahamВҰ106632 was declared guiltless becauseВҰ106631 of his actions, maybe heВҰ106636 could boastВҰ106637? But not towardsВҰ106640 \nd GodВҰ106642\nd*
\v 3 \x + \xo 4:3: \xt Gen 15:6; Gal 3:6.\x*becauseВҰ106644 the scripturesВҰ106646 say: вҖҳAbrahamВҰ106650 believedВҰ106648 in \nd GodВҰ106652\nd* so he was considered guiltless.вҖҷ
\v 4 Now for someone who's workingВҰ106660, their wages are considered вҖҳowedвҖҷ, not a gift.
\v 5 However someone who's not workingВҰ106687 butВҰ106685 having faith that \add God\add* will declare disobedient people as guiltless, then that person's faith is considered to make them guiltless.
\v 6 It's just like what DavidВҰ106710 said about blessingВҰ106713 a personВҰ106715 who \nd GodВҰ106718\nd* declares as guiltless despite their actions:
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 4:7-8: \xt Psa 32:1-2.\x*вҖҳThose who've been forgivenВҰ106725 for their lawlessnessВҰ106727 will be happy,
\q2 and whose sinsВҰ106732 have been coveredВҰ106730 over.
\q1
\v 8 Anyone who \nd YahwehВҰ106740\nd* declares to have no sinВҰ106741 will be happy.вҖҷ
