\p
\v 9 And as DavidВҰ110235 wrote:\x + \xo 11:9-10: \xt Psa 69:22-23 (LXX).\x*
\q1 вҖҳLet theirВҰ110240 tableВҰ110239 becomeВҰ110237 a trap for themвҖ”
\q2 a temptation that will pay them back.
\q1
\v 10 Let their eyesВҰ110255 be darkenedВҰ110253 so they can'tВҰ110258 see,
\q1 andВҰ110260 their backs be bent throughВҰ110264 all timeВҰ110265.вҖҷ
\rem /s1 The Salvation of the Gentiles; Ingrafted Branches
\p
\v 11 SoВҰ110268 now I ask: didn'tВҰ110269 they stumbleВҰ110270 so that they would fall? May itВҰ110274 never be. But because of theirВҰ110277 disobedience, salvationВҰ110280 came to non-Jews in order to make \add Jews\add* envious.
\v 12 ButВҰ110294 if their disobedience \add led to\add* gain for the \add rest of the\add* worldВҰ110293 andВҰ110294 if their loss \add led to\add* gain for the non-Jews, how much more their fullnessВҰ110303?
