\p
\v 13 But \add now\add* I am speakingВҰ110309 to youВҰ110305 all non-Jews. Since I am indeedВҰ110314 a missionary to the non-Jews, I take pride in myВҰ110323 ministry,
\v 14 hoping that somehowВҰ110327 I might make myВҰ110329 fellow Jews envious andВҰ110332 might saveВҰ110333 some of them.
\v 15 BecauseВҰ110338 if their rejectionВҰ110341 \add of the messiah\add* meant that \add the rest of\add* the worldВҰ110344 would be reconciledВҰ110343, what else could their acceptanceВҰ110348 bring other than \add coming back to\add* lifeВҰ110351 from the deadВҰ110353.
\p
\v 16 If the firstВҰ110358 portion \add of dough\add* is holy, so is the lump, andВҰ110363 if the root is holy, so are the branchesВҰ110370.
\v 17 ButВҰ110378 if some of the branchesВҰ110375 were brokenВҰ110376 off, and you \add non-Jews\add* who are like a wild, olive tree were grafted into them and so you too were able to share in the growth of the olive tree that was \add sourced\add* in the root,
\v 18 then don'tВҰ110394 brag that you're better than the branchesВҰ110397. If you must boast, remember that you're not supporting the root, butВҰ110399 the root is supporting you.
\p
\v 19 \add Ah,\add* but then you'll say, вҖҳBranches were brokenВҰ110414 off so that we could be grafted in.вҖҷ
\v 20 \add Well\add* you're right. They were brokenВҰ110424 off because of theirВҰ110421 unbeliefВҰ110422, and \add it's true\add* that you're there because of your faithВҰ110428. But don't get a big headвҖ”maintain your reverence \add for God\add*,
\v 21 becauseВҰ110438 if he didn'tВҰ110446 spare the naturalВҰ110443 branchesВҰ110445 \add when they showed unbelief\add*, then he won'tВҰ110446 spare you either.
\v 22 SoВҰ110454 you can both God's kindness and his severity: those who disobeyed \add experienced\add* his severity butВҰ110456 you \add experienced\add* his kindness. Otherwise you also will be pruned off,
\v 23 andВҰ110486 also if they turn from their unbeliefВҰ110492, they'll be grafted \add back\add* in, becauseВҰ110495 \nd GodВҰ110498\nd* has the powerВҰ110494 to do that.
\v 24 If were cut off an olive tree that's \em wild\em* by nature, and contraryВҰ110513 to normal practice were grafted into a \em cultivatedВҰ110517\em* olive tree, how much more would those who naturally belong be grafted into theirВҰ110525 own olive tree!
\s1 God's mercy is for everyone
